COGS are the direct costs of making the product (like materials and labor). How we used Colab and AI: We used Google Colab as our tool to write and run Python code. The AI acted like a tutor, breaking down the steps and providing a clear example. This showed me how AI can be a helpful assistant for learning new things and writing code, especially when you're just starting out!
